---
// FAQ section with JSON-LD schema
---

<section class="py-16 sm:py-20 bg-white">
	<div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
		<div class="text-center mb-12">
			<h2 class="font-display text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-bold text-gray-900 tracking-tight mb-4">
				Frequently Asked Questions
			</h2>
		</div>

		<div class="space-y-4" id="faq-accordion">
			<details class="group bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-xl overflow-hidden">
				<summary class="flex items-center justify-between px-5 py-4 cursor-pointer list-none hover:bg-gray-50 transition-colors">
					<span class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 pr-4">Is OrizPDF really free?</span>
					<svg class="size-5 text-gray-400 group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform shrink-0" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"/></svg>
				</summary>
				<div class="px-5 pb-4 text-sm text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">Yes, all tools are 100% free with no hidden fees, premium tiers, or account requirements. We believe everyone should have access to essential PDF tools.</div>
			</details>

			<details class="group bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-xl overflow-hidden">
				<summary class="flex items-center justify-between px-5 py-4 cursor-pointer list-none hover:bg-gray-50 transition-colors">
					<span class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 pr-4">Are my files uploaded to a server?</span>
					<svg class="size-5 text-gray-400 group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform shrink-0" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"/></svg>
				</summary>
				<div class="px-5 pb-4 text-sm text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">No. All PDF processing happens directly in your browser using WebAssembly and JavaScript. Your files never leave your device. We have no servers that receive your documents.</div>
			</details>

			<details class="group bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-xl overflow-hidden">
				<summary class="flex items-center justify-between px-5 py-4 cursor-pointer list-none hover:bg-gray-50 transition-colors">
					<span class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 pr-4">Do I need to create an account?</span>
					<svg class="size-5 text-gray-400 group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform shrink-0" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"/></svg>
				</summary>
				<div class="px-5 pb-4 text-sm text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">No account or registration is required. Simply open any tool and start using it immediately. The only exception is the AI Summarizer, which uses your free Puter.com account for AI features.</div>
			</details>

			<details class="group bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-xl overflow-hidden">
				<summary class="flex items-center justify-between px-5 py-4 cursor-pointer list-none hover:bg-gray-50 transition-colors">
					<span class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 pr-4">What file formats are supported?</span>
					<svg class="size-5 text-gray-400 group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform shrink-0" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"/></svg>
				</summary>
				<div class="px-5 pb-4 text-sm text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">We support PDF files as the primary format, plus JPG, PNG, WebP images, DOCX (Word), XLSX (Excel), and HTML for conversion tools. Each tool lists its specific supported formats.</div>
			</details>

			<details class="group bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-xl overflow-hidden">
				<summary class="flex items-center justify-between px-5 py-4 cursor-pointer list-none hover:bg-gray-50 transition-colors">
					<span class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 pr-4">Is there a file size limit?</span>
					<svg class="size-5 text-gray-400 group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform shrink-0" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"/></svg>
				</summary>
				<div class="px-5 pb-4 text-sm text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">The maximum file size is 100MB per file. This limit exists because processing happens in your browser, and very large files may exceed available memory. Most typical documents are well under this limit.</div>
			</details>

			<details class="group bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-xl overflow-hidden">
				<summary class="flex items-center justify-between px-5 py-4 cursor-pointer list-none hover:bg-gray-50 transition-colors">
					<span class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 pr-4">Does it work on mobile devices?</span>
					<svg class="size-5 text-gray-400 group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform shrink-0" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"/></svg>
				</summary>
				<div class="px-5 pb-4 text-sm text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">Yes! OrizPDF works on all modern browsers including Chrome, Firefox, Safari, and Edge on desktop, tablet, and mobile devices. The interface is fully responsive and touch-friendly.</div>
			</details>

			<details class="group bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-xl overflow-hidden">
				<summary class="flex items-center justify-between px-5 py-4 cursor-pointer list-none hover:bg-gray-50 transition-colors">
					<span class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 pr-4">Can I use OrizPDF for commercial purposes?</span>
					<svg class="size-5 text-gray-400 group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform shrink-0" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"/></svg>
				</summary>
				<div class="px-5 pb-4 text-sm text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">Yes. OrizPDF is free for both personal and commercial use. There are no usage limits or restrictions on the type of documents you can process.</div>
			</details>

			<details class="group bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-xl overflow-hidden">
				<summary class="flex items-center justify-between px-5 py-4 cursor-pointer list-none hover:bg-gray-50 transition-colors">
					<span class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 pr-4">How does the AI Summarizer work?</span>
					<svg class="size-5 text-gray-400 group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform shrink-0" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"/></svg>
				</summary>
				<div class="px-5 pb-4 text-sm text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">The AI Summarizer extracts text from your PDF and sends it to AI models via Puter.js. Puter.js provides free AI with a user-pays model — you sign in with a free Puter account, and the AI processing is covered by Puter. Your text is sent to the AI provider for analysis but is not stored by OrizPDF.</div>
			</details>

			<details class="group bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-xl overflow-hidden">
				<summary class="flex items-center justify-between px-5 py-4 cursor-pointer list-none hover:bg-gray-50 transition-colors">
					<span class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 pr-4">What browsers are supported?</span>
					<svg class="size-5 text-gray-400 group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform shrink-0" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"/></svg>
				</summary>
				<div class="px-5 pb-4 text-sm text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">OrizPDF works on all modern browsers: Chrome 90+, Firefox 88+, Safari 15+, and Edge 90+. We recommend using the latest version of your browser for the best experience.</div>
			</details>

			<details class="group bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-xl overflow-hidden">
				<summary class="flex items-center justify-between px-5 py-4 cursor-pointer list-none hover:bg-gray-50 transition-colors">
					<span class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 pr-4">Is OrizPDF open source?</span>
					<svg class="size-5 text-gray-400 group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform shrink-0" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"/></svg>
				</summary>
				<div class="px-5 pb-4 text-sm text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">Yes! OrizPDF is fully open source under the MIT license. You can view the source code, contribute, or self-host it on your own infrastructure.</div>
			</details>
		</div>
	</div>
</section>

<script type="application/ld+json">
{
	"@context": "https://schema.org",
	"@type": "FAQPage",
	"mainEntity": [
		{
			"@type": "Question",
			"name": "Is OrizPDF really free?",
			"acceptedAnswer": {
				"@type": "Answer",
				"text": "Yes, all tools are 100% free with no hidden fees, premium tiers, or account requirements."
			}
		},
		{
			"@type": "Question",
			"name": "Are my files uploaded to a server?",
			"acceptedAnswer": {
				"@type": "Answer",
				"text": "No. All PDF processing happens directly in your browser using WebAssembly and JavaScript. Your files never leave your device."
			}
		},
		{
			"@type": "Question",
			"name": "Do I need to create an account?",
			"acceptedAnswer": {
				"@type": "Answer",
				"text": "No account or registration is required. Simply open any tool and start using it immediately."
			}
		},
		{
			"@type": "Question",
			"name": "What file formats are supported?",
			"acceptedAnswer": {
				"@type": "Answer",
				"text": "We support PDF files, JPG, PNG, WebP images, DOCX (Word), XLSX (Excel), and HTML for conversion tools."
			}
		},
		{
			"@type": "Question",
			"name": "Is there a file size limit?",
			"acceptedAnswer": {
				"@type": "Answer",
				"text": "The maximum file size is 100MB per file, since processing happens in your browser."
			}
		}
	]
}
</script>
